RSYSLOG

This little progam writes a message to a remote log on some remote
machine.

Synopsis:

$ rsyslog [<loghost>] [<recipient(s)>] [-f <from>] [-if <infile>] 
	[-p <priority>] [-t <tag>] [-af <afile>]

where:

<loghost>	log host
<recipient(s)>	one or more recipients in the form:
			loghost[:username]
		or
			username@loghost
-af <afile>	file containging recipients, one per line
-if <infile>	input file to send out
-p <priority>	priority of message
-t <tag>	tag associated with message
-V		print program version to standard-error and then exit

